WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:06.573 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
♪

00:20.887 --> 00:21.955 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
♪

00:25.058 --> 00:26.326 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
>> NARRATOR: Yemen.

00:29.529 --> 00:30.997 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
Journalist Safa al Ahmad
has been covering

00:31.031 --> 00:34.334 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
the devastating war here since
it began four years ago.

00:37.871 --> 00:41.641 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
Now she's come to investigate a
different conflict:

00:41.674 --> 00:45.311 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
the escalation of the U.S. fight
against Al Qaeda in Yemen.

00:48.148 --> 00:49.949 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's been little reporting
from the ground

00:49.983 --> 00:54.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
about what the U.S.
is doing here.

00:54.320 --> 00:57.857 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But one operation made headlines
two years ago.

00:57.891 --> 00:59.359 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> U.S. forces launched a
surprise raid

00:59.392 --> 01:00.960 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in Yemen overnight...

01:00.994 --> 01:03.596 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> ...targeting an Al Qaeda camp
in southern Yemen on Sunday...

01:03.630 --> 01:07.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> ...the pre-dawn raid went
wrong almost from the beginning,

01:07.100 --> 01:09.769 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
leaving a Navy SEAL dead.

01:09.803 --> 01:13.673 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> A highly successful raid that
will lead to many more victories

01:13.706 --> 01:17.577 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in the future against our enemy.

01:17.610 --> 01:19.612 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> AHMAD: I was hearing reports
questioning how successful

01:19.646 --> 01:21.915 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that mission was,
and I was also hearing about

01:21.948 --> 01:23.650 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
civilian casualties.

01:23.683 --> 01:25.552 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I wanted to go and see for
myself

01:25.585 --> 01:29.289 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what had happened that night,
but also what it might reveal

01:29.322 --> 01:32.025 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
about the larger
counterterrorism operation

01:32.058 --> 01:33.827 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that the U.S. were conducting.

01:33.860 --> 01:37.197 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
(gun fires, explosion roars)

01:37.230 --> 01:39.132 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: Yemen has been
wracked by a war

01:39.165 --> 01:43.136 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
between armed factions
since 2014.

01:43.169 --> 01:45.772 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
(crowd chanting):

01:47.774 --> 01:50.510 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On one side: the Houthis,
a group from Northern Yemen

01:50.543 --> 01:53.413 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with links to Iran.

01:53.446 --> 01:55.181 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Against them: many tribes,

01:55.215 --> 01:59.486 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and a coalition including Yemeni
government troops, Saudi Arabia,

01:59.519 --> 02:04.324 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
and the UAE,
supported by the U.S.

02:04.357 --> 02:06.860 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
At the same time, the U.S. has
been trying to target

02:06.893 --> 02:10.663 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
both ISIS and Al Qaeda here.

02:10.697 --> 02:15.735 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
The Navy SEAL raid in January
2017 was on the village of Yakla

02:15.768 --> 02:19.472 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
on the front line between
the tribes and the Houthis.

02:22.342 --> 02:23.943 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> AHMAD: Since I heard about
the Yakla raid,

02:23.977 --> 02:28.381 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I've been trying for months
to get access to the village.

02:28.414 --> 02:31.351 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I finally got a phone call--
I was going to be picked up

02:31.384 --> 02:34.954 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by somebody from Yakla village
and be driven there.

02:38.391 --> 02:40.426 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Yakla is a very dangerous place
to get to

02:40.460 --> 02:43.930 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because it sits in the middle
of several front lines.

02:43.963 --> 02:46.399 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
You have the Houthis,
you have the tribes,

02:46.432 --> 02:49.169 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
and you have the Yemeni
government fighting there.

02:49.202 --> 02:51.137 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
You also have elements
of Al Qaeda,

02:51.171 --> 02:54.107 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
and so this exposes everyone
to the danger

02:54.140 --> 02:55.808 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
of U.S. drone strikes.

03:00.513 --> 03:02.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On the way, the driver stopped
in a clearing

03:02.515 --> 03:04.417 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
where he told me that this is
where

03:04.450 --> 03:07.820 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the American Special Forces
had landed.

03:11.858 --> 03:14.827 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They had trekked for seven
kilometers to the village

03:14.861 --> 03:19.065 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Yakla, and so we had retraced
their trip to the village.

03:30.577 --> 03:33.346 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(hammering, clattering)

03:34.881 --> 03:36.983 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
>> NARRATOR:
The Navy SEALs attacked

03:37.016 --> 03:38.785 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
an Al Qaeda headquarters here,

03:38.818 --> 03:42.755 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
according to a Pentagon
statement.

03:42.789 --> 03:45.959 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The statement said the troops
met resistance,

03:45.992 --> 03:49.996 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
including from numerous
female fighters.

03:50.029 --> 03:54.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One American soldier was killed
and three others injured.

03:54.167 --> 03:59.872 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The military said they killed at
least 14 Al Qaeda members.

03:59.906 --> 04:01.374 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> AHMAD: I wanted to talk
to the eyewitnesses

04:01.407 --> 04:03.876 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that had survived the raid

04:03.910 --> 04:07.780 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to hear their narrative about
what happened.

04:11.651 --> 04:14.554 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
ABDULILLAH AL DAHAB:

04:18.224 --> 04:21.995 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: Local tribal leader
Sheikh Abdulillah al Dahab

04:22.028 --> 04:24.097 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has been in hiding since the
raid

04:24.130 --> 04:27.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and has not been interviewed
about what happened until now.

04:29.302 --> 04:32.672 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
DAHAB:

04:38.311 --> 04:41.147 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: He says his tribe
has been fighting the Houthis

04:41.180 --> 04:45.084 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
on the side backed
by the United States.

04:45.118 --> 04:49.789 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
DAHAB:

04:53.760 --> 04:56.129 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: At 2:00 a.m.,
Abdulillah says

04:56.162 --> 04:58.531 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
his 11-year-old son Ahmed
was on their roof

04:58.564 --> 05:01.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and saw armed men approaching.

05:01.100 --> 05:04.704 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Thinking they were Houthis,
the boy shouted out.

05:04.737 --> 05:07.040 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The sheikh says the commandos
then shot Ahmed

05:07.073 --> 05:12.912 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
through the heart, and his
family returned fire.

05:12.945 --> 05:16.082 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
DAHAB:

05:54.120 --> 05:57.523 align:left position:25%,start line:0% size:75%
AHMAD and SINAN:

06:03.663 --> 06:05.565 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> AHMAD: The people of Yakla
told me that at least

06:05.598 --> 06:08.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
seven women and ten children
were killed that night.

06:08.101 --> 06:11.804 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
The youngest was
a three-month-old.

06:11.838 --> 06:14.974 align:left position:25%,start line:0% size:75%
MILHA AL AMERI:

06:25.818 --> 06:28.421 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: The Pentagon
acknowledged that civilians,

06:28.454 --> 06:30.223 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
including children, were likely
killed

06:30.256 --> 06:34.160 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in what they called
a "ferocious firefight."

06:34.193 --> 06:37.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But they said the Navy SEALs had
obtained valuable intelligence

06:37.864 --> 06:40.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and taken out Al Qaeda leaders--

06:40.400 --> 06:44.971 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
including two of Abdulillah's
brothers.

06:45.004 --> 06:47.173 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The sheikh denies the brothers
had anything to do

06:47.206 --> 06:49.575 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with Al Qaeda.

06:49.609 --> 06:52.078 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He says one of them,
Abdul Raouf,

06:52.111 --> 06:54.947 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
was a tribal commander
with the Yemeni army,

06:54.981 --> 06:56.783 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the side backed by the U.S.

06:56.816 --> 06:58.718 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This was confirmed
to "Frontline"

06:58.751 --> 07:00.820 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
by the Yemeni government.

07:00.853 --> 07:03.589 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
DAHAB:

07:14.534 --> 07:16.102 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
>> NARRATOR: The sheikh
acknowledges

07:16.135 --> 07:19.839 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that members of his family have
been connected to Al Qaeda.

07:19.872 --> 07:21.574 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> AHMAD: The Dahab family is
symbolic

07:21.607 --> 07:25.044 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the complexities
of Yemeni politics.

07:25.077 --> 07:28.481 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have people of his family
who did choose to join Al Qaeda.

07:28.514 --> 07:32.318 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have members who did not
and chose to fight them.

07:37.356 --> 07:39.392 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: The sheikh's
brother-in-law

07:39.425 --> 07:42.395 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
was Anwar al Awlaki, the
Yemeni-American Al Qaeda leader

07:42.428 --> 07:49.402 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who was killed in a drone strike
in 2011.

07:49.435 --> 07:51.337 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Al Awlaki's eight-year-old
daughter Nawar,

07:51.370 --> 07:55.675 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the sheikh's niece,
was killed in the Yakla raid.

07:55.708 --> 08:01.814 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The family said she was shot
in the neck.

08:01.848 --> 08:04.550 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> AHMAD: The members of the
Dahab family that I spoke to

08:04.584 --> 08:08.321 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
told me they had paid a really
high price

08:08.354 --> 08:10.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
just because they were part
of the Dahab family.

08:13.092 --> 08:17.997 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: The villagers say
around 30 civilians were killed.

08:18.030 --> 08:21.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
Most are buried in this
cemetery.

08:21.334 --> 08:24.036 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
Department of Defense
investigations later concluded

08:24.070 --> 08:28.307 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
that there were between four
and 12 civilian casualties

08:28.341 --> 08:32.378 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
and and around 35 enemy
combatants killed.

08:32.411 --> 08:35.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:0% size:87.5%
They would not comment
on the Sheikh's brothers,

08:35.181 --> 08:38.217 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
and told "Frontline" they
maintain "a firm commitment

08:38.251 --> 08:40.820 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
to protecting civilians."

08:40.853 --> 08:42.622 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
♪

08:46.025 --> 08:47.693 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Yakla raid marked
the beginning

08:47.727 --> 08:50.630 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of a dramatic escalation
of the U.S.'s ongoing war

08:50.663 --> 08:54.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
against Al Qaeda in Yemen.

08:54.700 --> 08:57.336 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
During President Obama's
eight years in office,

08:57.370 --> 09:01.474 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the U.S. carried out an
estimated 154 drone strikes

09:01.507 --> 09:03.809 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Yemen.

09:03.843 --> 09:06.579 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
In President Trump's
first two years,

09:06.612 --> 09:09.415 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
around 176 have been reported.

09:11.484 --> 09:13.319 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
>> A priority is the fight
against Al Qaeda

09:13.352 --> 09:15.388 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
in the Arabian Peninsula.

09:15.421 --> 09:20.826 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
>> This is a franchised Al Qaeda
metastasizing threat.

09:20.860 --> 09:23.362 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
>> This is the franchise of
Al Qaeda that has demonstrated

09:23.396 --> 09:28.067 align:left position:0%,start line:0% size:100%
the ability to try to attack
our homeland.

09:31.137 --> 09:32.471 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: The roads leading
out of Yakla

09:32.505 --> 09:35.241 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are littered with the wreckage
of cars destroyed

09:35.274 --> 09:39.912 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
by drone strikes.

09:39.946 --> 09:41.514 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
>> AHMAD: While I was in Yemen,

09:41.547 --> 09:45.351 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I heard about a drone strike
that had just recently happened.

09:45.384 --> 09:48.955 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was in the central region
of Shabwa.

09:48.988 --> 09:51.824 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It all started apparently when
a boy had joined

09:51.857 --> 09:53.593 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Al Qaeda.

09:53.626 --> 09:57.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
(dog barking, Ahmad and Ali
Salem speaking Arabic)

09:57.863 --> 09:59.765 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
AHMAD:

09:59.799 --> 10:04.870 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: Ali Salem is the
uncle of the boy.

10:04.904 --> 10:09.075 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He takes Safa to meet him.

10:09.108 --> 10:13.479 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For his safety, we agreed not
to show his face.

10:13.512 --> 10:17.016 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He says he ran away from home
with friends to join Al Qaeda.

10:18.017 --> 10:19.619 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
AHMAD:

10:19.652 --> 10:21.621 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
BOY:

10:26.192 --> 10:28.861 align:left position:25%,start line:0% size:75%
AHMAD and BOY:

10:34.433 --> 10:36.969 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
♪

10:37.003 --> 10:39.605 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: Al Qaeda in Yemen
doesn't just preach jihad

10:39.639 --> 10:41.707 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
against the United States,

10:41.741 --> 10:45.578 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but also against the UAE forces,
Saudis, and the Houthis,

10:45.611 --> 10:49.048 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
all of whom they consider
infidels.

10:49.081 --> 10:52.418 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> AHMAD: The situation in Yemen
is very complex right now.

10:52.451 --> 10:56.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have interlocking conflicts
of who is fighting who.

10:56.222 --> 10:57.857 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The people on the ground have
told me

10:57.890 --> 11:00.126 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that many of these young men
who join Al Qaeda

11:00.159 --> 11:02.428 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are joining it for local
reasons,

11:02.461 --> 11:05.464 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for local conflicts, and not
necessarily because

11:05.498 --> 11:09.535 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
they want to join
the global jihad.

11:09.568 --> 11:11.437 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
>> NARRATOR: According
to villagers in Shabwa,

11:11.470 --> 11:16.242 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on January 26, 2018, the boy's
father and some relatives

11:16.275 --> 11:21.180 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
set out by car to rescue the boy
from Al Qaeda.

11:21.213 --> 11:26.752 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
While driving,
they came under attack.

11:26.786 --> 11:29.855 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
BOY:

11:39.131 --> 11:42.268 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
SALEM:

12:04.590 --> 12:07.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: The family says
seven relatives were killed

12:07.326 --> 12:09.729 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the strike.

12:15.935 --> 12:18.370 align:left position:37.5%,start line:0% size:62.5%
SALEM:

12:22.675 --> 12:25.444 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: Ali is a soldier in
the Yemeni army.

12:25.478 --> 12:28.614 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He says the boy's father
was a taxi driver

12:28.647 --> 12:30.583 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and two other uncles
who were killed

12:30.616 --> 12:32.651 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
were also in the Yemeni army.

12:34.120 --> 12:37.389 align:left position:25%,start line:0% size:75%
AHMAD AND SALEM:

12:59.945 --> 13:01.847 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
>> NARRATOR: Ali Salem prepared
these papers

13:01.881 --> 13:04.450 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to clear the names
of his relatives.

13:04.483 --> 13:07.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He wants the U.S. to pay
compensation for their deaths.

13:07.987 --> 13:09.955 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He says he is now
the sole provider

13:09.989 --> 13:16.562 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for over 30 family members.

13:16.595 --> 13:18.631 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We asked the Pentagon
about the strike

13:18.664 --> 13:21.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and Ali Salem's account
of the deaths.

13:21.500 --> 13:24.570 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But they would not comment
beyond a statement at the time

13:24.603 --> 13:26.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
